condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Financial management | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall maintain a financial management systemand prepare interim unaudited financial reports for the Project at the end of each calendar semester in form and substanceacceptable to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Financial reports | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall furnish the audited financial statementsto the Bank and the Borrower not later than six months after the end of each fiscal year of the Project Implementing Entity. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Implementation arrangements | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall maintain throughout the periodof implementation of the project an organizational structure satisfactory to the Bank including a Project Leading Group responsiblefor overseeing implementation, making decision on key projectsissues and carrying out interagency coordination; and a ProjectManagement Office responsible for project management and implementation. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Integration Plan | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall implement, through NM, the IntegrationPlan, as approved, or as adjusted when required, in consultation with the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Reporting | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Projectand prepare Project Reports based on Section5.08 (b) of the General Conditions, including project indicators, and furnish thesemi-annual Project Reports to the Bank by March 31 and September 30 each year, beginning on September 30, 2013. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Safeguards | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall cause NM and URC to implement the SafeguardsInstruments in a manner and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: Intermediate Result Indicator Seven: Number of TAs completed (cumulative)
Intermediate Result Indicator Six: Accessibility – percentage of stations with barrier-free accessibility to the wheel-chair boundand sight impaired
Intermediate Result Indicator Four: Level of integration in terms of bus routes reorganized to reflect Line 2 opening
Indicator Two: Reduced travel time on public transport modes along Line 2 corridor
Sub-Indicator One: Reduced travel time on public transport modes along High Speed Rail station to Nanchang Railway station
Sub-Indicator Two: Reduced travel time on public transport modes along XinJiaAn station to WoLongShan station
Sub-Indicator Three: Reduced travel time on public transport modes along High Speed Rail station to Metro Mansion station
Indicator Three: Percentage of urban rail commuters along Line 2 with access to a car
Indicator One: Line 2 Ridership (Passenger-trips per weekday)
Intermediate Result Indicator Three: Level of integration in terms of facilities for bus/rail/bike transfer designed and constructed in line with integration plan
Intermediate Result Indicator One: Percentage of construction of stations (in value)
Intermediate Result Indicator Two: Percentage of completion of tunnels (in value)
Indicator Four: Percentage of users that rate the service “satisfactory” on average (also recorded for each gender for reference)
Intermediate Result Indicator Five: Level of integration in terms of availability of a single payment card for rail and bus
